ericclemmons:
I found this via Google & had the same issue.  This messes up when you try to call setState while rendering on the server.  (I found out the hard way with react-resolver that setState cannot run on the server-side!)
Anyway, here was my offending code:
``` javascript
componentWillMount() {
  setInterval(updateTime, 1000);
}
updateTime() {
  this.setState({ time: new Date() });
}
```
Remember that componentWillMount runs on both server & client.  Moving the code to componentDidMount, which only happens on the client solved the problem!

http://facebook.github.io/react/docs/component-specs.html#mounting-componentwillmount
